<TITLE> DoE moves against industrial polluters </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 21 (bdnews24.com)  A joint DoE and BSTI drive on Monday took punitive measures, including Tk 320,000 in fines and filing cases, against nine factories in Gazipur and Tongi for pollution and failure to comply with industrial standards. Of the nine, three factories face cases for failure to use Effluent Treatment Plants (ETPs) A mobile court fined Orbit Processing Mills Ltd in Tongi Tk 80,000 on the spot as its ETP was ineffective. The court also discovered Pacific Fibre Corporation without any ETP and Angel Composite Knitting Industries Ltd with a faulty ETP, both in Gazipur. Jamshed Hossain, director of the department of environment's Dhaka divisional office, said preparations are on to file cases against all three. Four brick factories in GazipurTaslim Bricks Manufacturing Ltd faced Tk 50,000, Mahbub Enterprise and Siraj & Co Tk 70,000 each, and Farid & Co Tk 50,000were fined for failure to comply with BSTI standards in the manufacture of their bricks. Punitive steps were also taken against Crossline Knitting Fabrics Ltd in Gazipur and Ecocom BD (Pvt) Ltd in Tongi for pollution. Hossain headed the mobile court operations; magistrates Md Nazmul Hassan and Abul Bashar Md Amiruddin accompanied him. Officials of the Bangladesh Standards and Testing Institute and police assisted them. Drives will be continued against industrial pollution and non-compliance with industrial standards, the DoE said in a statement. bdnews24.com/c
